= class Gdk::PixbufSimpleAnim

((*Since 2.8*))

== Object Hierarchy

* Object
  * GLib::Instantiatable
    * GLib::Object
      * Gdk::PixbufAnimation
        * Gdk::PixbufSimpleAnim

== Class Methods

--- Gdk::PixbufSimpleAnim.new(width, height, rate)

    Creates a new, empty animation. ((*Since 2.8*))
    * width: the width of the animation (Fixnum)
    * height: the height of the animation (Fixnum)
    * rate: the speed of the animation, in frames per second (Float)
    * Returns: a newly-created Gdk::PixbufSimpleAnim

== Instance Methods

--- add_frame(pixbuf)

    Adds a new frame to self. The Gdk::Pixbuf passed must have the dimensions specified when the animation was constructed. ((*Since 2.8*))
    * pixbuf: the Gdk::Pixbuf to add
    * Returns: self

--- loop=(loop)

    Sets the value whether the animation should loop when it reaches the end or not.
     * loop: true if the animation should loop when it reaches the end
     * Returns: loop

--- loop?

    Gets the value whether the animation should loop when it reaches the end or not.
     * Returns: true if the animation should loop when it reaches the end

--- set_loop(loop)

    Same as loop=.
     * loop: true if the animation should loop when it reaches the end
     * Returns: self

== Properties

--- loop: true or false (Read/Write)

    Whether the animation should loop when it reaches the end

== See Also

Gdk::PixbufAnimation

== ChangeLog

-((<gc>))
